### PoBabyTouch API Tests
### Use with REST Client extension in VS Code
### Base URL for local development
@baseUrl = https://localhost:7001
@apiUrl = {{baseUrl}}/api

### ============================================================
### Health Checks
### ============================================================

### Get API Health Status
GET {{apiUrl}}/health
Accept: application/json

### ============================================================
### High Scores - Retrieval
### ============================================================

### Get Top 10 High Scores (Default Mode)
GET {{apiUrl}}/highscores?count=10&gameMode=Default
Accept: application/json

### Get Top 5 High Scores (Easy Mode)
GET {{apiUrl}}/highscores?count=5&gameMode=Easy
Accept: application/json

### Check if Score Qualifies as High Score
GET {{apiUrl}}/highscores/check/2500?gameMode=Default
Accept: application/json

### Get Player Rank for Score
GET {{apiUrl}}/highscores/rank/1500?gameMode=Default
Accept: application/json

### ============================================================
### High Scores - Submission
### ============================================================

### Save New High Score
POST {{apiUrl}}/highscores
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "playerInitials": "ABC",
  "score": 2500,
  "gameMode": "Default"
}

### Save High Score - Invalid (Too Short)
POST {{apiUrl}}/highscores
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "playerInitials": "AB",
  "score": 1500,
  "gameMode": "Default"
}

### Save High Score - Invalid (Negative Score)
POST {{apiUrl}}/highscores
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "playerInitials": "XYZ",
  "score": -100,
  "gameMode": "Default"
}

### ============================================================
### High Scores - Diagnostics
### ============================================================

### Test High Score Service Connection
GET {{apiUrl}}/highscores/test
Accept: application/json

### Get High Score Service Diagnostics
GET {{apiUrl}}/highscores/diagnostics
Accept: application/json

### ============================================================
### Client Logging
### ============================================================

### Post Client Log (Info)
POST {{apiUrl}}/log/client
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "Test log from REST client",
  "level": "Information",
  "category": "Test",
  "timestamp": "{{$datetime iso8601}}",
  "sessionId": "test-session-123",
  "userId": null,
  "gameMode": "Default",
  "data": {
    "testKey": "testValue"
  }
}

### Post Client Log (Error)
POST {{apiUrl}}/log/client
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "Test error log",
  "level": "Error",
  "category": "Test",
  "timestamp": "{{$datetime iso8601}}",
  "sessionId": "test-session-123",
  "userId": null,
  "gameMode": null,
  "data": null
}
